{\\'e}ratures in Systems with Slow Dynamics},\n  author = {Cugliandolo, L. F. and Kurchan, J. and Peliti, L.},\n  year = {1997},\n  journal = {Phys. Rev. E},\n  volume = {55},\n  pages = {3898}\n}\n","metadata":{"DeclarePrefChars":"","noopsort":false,"packages":[]},"meta":{"revision":0,"created":1751534256134,"version":0,"updated":1753730283776},"$loki":1250},{"exportNotes":false,"useJournalAbbreviation":true,"bibtexURL":"off","DOIandURL":"both","itemID":26085,"entry":"@article{cugliandoloFluctuationDissipationTheoremsEntropy1997,\n  title = {Fluctuation-{{Dissipation Theorems}} and {{Entropy Production}} in {{Relaxational Systems}}},\n  author = {Cugliandolo, L. F. and Dean, D. S. and Kurchan, J.},\n  year = {1997},\n  journal = {Phys. Rev. Lett.},\n  volume = {79},\n  pages = {2168--2171}\n}\n","metadata":{"DeclarePrefChars":"","noopsort":false,"packages":[]},"meta":{"revision":0,"created":1751534256136,"version":0,"updated":1753730283776},"$loki":1251},{"exportNotes":false,"useJournalAbbreviation":true,"bibtexURL":"off","DOIandURL":"both","itemID":26646,"entry":"@article{cugliandoloOutEquilibriumDynamics1994,\n  title = {On the out of Equilibrium Dynamics of the Long-Range {{Sherrington-Kirkpatrick}} Model},\n  author = {Cugliandolo, L. F. and Kurchan, J.},\n  year = {1994},\n  journal = {J. Phys. A},\n  volume = {27},\n  pages = {5749}\n}\n","metadata":{"DeclarePrefChars":"","noopsort":false,"packages":[]},"meta":{"revision":0,"created":1751534256136,"version":0,"updated":1753730283776},"$loki":1252},{"exportNotes":false,"useJournalAbbreviation":true,"bibtexURL":"off","DOIandURL":"both","itemID":26741,"entry":"@article{cunhaPolymerMediatedCompactionInternal2001,\n  title = {Polymer-{{Mediated Compaction}} and {{Internal Dynamics}} of {{Isolated}} {{{\\emph{Escherichia Coli}}}} Nucleoids},\n  author = {Cunha, S. and Woldringh, C. L. and Odijk, T.},\n  year = {2001},\n  journal = {J. Struct. Biol.},\n  volume = {136},\n  number = {1},\n  pages = {53}\n}\n","metadata":{"DeclarePrefChars":"","noopsort":false,"packages":[]},"meta":{"revision":0,"created":1751534256138,"version":0,"updated":1753730283776},"$loki":1253},{"exportNotes":false,"useJournalAbbreviation":true,"bibtexURL":"off","DOIandURL":"both","itemID":26774,"entry":"@article{daboraMicrotubuledependentFormationTubulovesicular1988,\n  title = {The Microtubule-Dependent Formation of a Tubulovesicular Network with Characteristics of the {{ER}} from Cultured Cell Extracts},\n  author = {Dabora, Sandra L. and Sheetz, Michael F.},\n  year = {1988},\n  month = jul,\n  journal = {Cell},\n  volume = {54},\n  number = {1},\n  pages = {27--35},\n  issn = {00928674},\n  doi = {10.1016/0092-8674(88)90176-6},\n  urldate = {2025-05-08},\n  abstract = {The formation of a dynamic tubulovesicular membrane network that resembles the endoplasmic reticulum (ER) has been observed in extracts of cultured chick embryo fibroblasts (CEF cells) using videoenhanced differential interference contrast microscopy. Initially, membranes in the CEF extracts appeared amorphous and aggregated, but with time, membrane tubules moved out along stationary microtubules. The membrane tubules formed new branches on intersecting microtubules and fused with other branches to form a network of interconnected polygons. The tubulovesicular network was solubilized by detergent and took on a beaded morphology in a hypotonic buffer. Formation of the tubulovesicular network required ATP and microtubules. The network did not contain elements of the plasma membrane, Golgi apparatus, or mitochondria but could be labeled with ER markers. We suggest that the tubulovesicular network contains components from the ER and is formed by membrane associated motors moving upon microtubules in a process we call microtubuledependent tethering.},\n  copyright = {https://www.elsevier.com/tdm/userlicense/1.0/},\n  langid = {english},\n  file = {/Users/michelecastellana/Zotero/storage/5UAT6663/Dabora and Sheetz - 1988 - The microtubule-dependent formation of a tubuloves.pdf}\n}\n","metadata":{"DeclarePrefChars":"","noopsort":false,"packages":[]},"meta":{"revision":0,"created":1751534256142,"version":0,"updated":1753730283776},"$loki":1254},{"exportNotes":false,"useJournalAbbreviation":true,"bibtexURL":"off","DOIandURL":"both","itemID":26004,"entry":"@article{dallastaEntropyLandscapeNonGibbs2008,\n  title = {Entropy Landscape and Non-{{Gibbs}} Solutions in Constraint Satisfaction Problems},\n  author = {Dall'Asta, L. and Ramezanpour, A. and Zecchina, R.},\n  year = {2008},\n  journal = {Phys. Rev. E},\n  volume = {77},\n  pages = {031118}\n}\n","metadata":{"DeclarePrefChars":"","noopsort":false,"packages":[]},"meta":{"revision":0,"created":1751534256142,"version":0,"updated":1753730283776},"$loki":1255},{"exportNotes":false,"useJournalAbbreviation":true,"bibtexURL":"off","DOIandURL":"both","itemID":26231,"entry":"@phdthesis{dammInterplayConformationalDynamics2019,\n  title = {Interplay between the Conformational Dynamics of a Transmembrane Protein and the Mechanical Properties of Its Surrounding Membrane},\n  author = {Damm, A.},\n  year = {2019}\n}\n","metadata":{"DeclarePrefChars":"","noopsort":false,"packages":[]},"meta":{"revision":0,"created":1751534256143,"version":0,"updated":1753730283776},"$loki":1256},{"exportNotes":false,"useJournalAbbreviation":true,"bibtexURL":"off","DOIandURL":"both","itemID":25928,"entry":"@article{danielsCurvatureCorrectionMobility2016,\n  title = {Curvature Correction to the Mobility of Fluid Membrane Inclusions},\n  author = {Daniels, D. R.},\n  year = {2016},\n  month = oct,\n  journal = {Eur. Phys. J. E},\n  volume = {39},\n  number = {10},\n  pages = {96},\n  issn = {1292-8941, 1292-895X},\n  doi = {10.1140/epje/i2016-16096-3},\n  urldate = {2025-02-19},\n  langid = {english},\n  file = {/Users/michelecastellana/Zotero/storage/NCHVD3NN/Daniels - 2016 - Curvature correction to the mobility of fluid membrane inclusions.pdf}\n}\n","metadata":{"DeclarePrefChars":"","noopsort":false,"packages":[]},"meta":{"revision":0,"created":1751534256143,"version":0,"updated":1753730283776},"$loki":1257},{"exportNotes":false,"useJournalAbbreviation":true,"bibtexURL":"off","DOIandURL":"both","itemID":26664,"entry":"@article{datsenkoOnestepInactivationChromasomal2000,\n  title = {One-Step Inactivation of Chromasomal Genes in {{{\\emph{E}}}}scherichia Coli {{K-12}} Using {{PCR}} Products},\n  author = {Datsenko, K. A. and Wanner, B. L.},\n  year = {2000},\n  journal = {P. Nat. Acad. Sci. USA},\n  volume = {97},\n  number = {12},\n  pages = {6640}\n}\n","metadata":{"DeclarePrefChars":"","noopsort":false,"packages":[]},"meta":{"revision":0,"created":1751534256144,"version":0,"updated":1753730283776},"$loki":1258},{"exportNotes":false,"useJournalAbbreviation":true,"bibtexURL":"off","DOIandURL":"both","itemID":26699,"entry":"@article{daudePairsSATAssignments2008,\n  title = {Pairs of {{SAT Assignments}} and {{Clustering}} in {{Random Boolean Formulae}}},\n  author = {Daud{\\'e}, H. and Mora, T. and M{\\'e}zard, M. and Zecchina, R.},\n  year = {2008},\n  journal = {Theoretical Computer Science},\n  volume = {393},\n  pages = {260--279}\n}\n","metadata":{"DeclarePrefChars":"","noopsort":false,"packages":[]},"meta":{"revision":0,"created":1751534256144,"version":0,"updated":1753730283776},"$loki":1259},{"exportNotes":false,"useJournalAbbreviation":true,"bibtexURL":"off","DOIandURL":"both","itemID":26679,"entry":"@book{davidOrderStatistics2003,\n  title = {Order {{Statistics}}},\n  author = {David, H. A. and Nagaraja, H. N.},\n  year = {2003},\n  publisher = {{Wiley-Interscience}},\n  abstract = {This volume provides an up-to-date coverage of the theory and applications of ordered random variables and their functions. Furthermore, it develops the distribution theory of OS systematically. Applications include procedures for the treatment of outliers and other data analysis techniques. Even when chapter and section headings are the same as in OSII, there are appreciable changes, mostly additions, with some obvious deletions. Parts of old Ch. 7, for example, are prime candidates for omission. Appendices are designed to help collate tables, computer algorithms, and software, as well as to compile related monographs on the subject matter. Extensive exercise sets will continue, many of them replaced by newer ones.}\n}\n","metadata":{"DeclarePrefChars":"","noopsort":false,"packages":[]},"meta":{"revision":0,"created":1751534256145,"version":0,"updated":1753730283776},"$loki":1260},{"exportNotes":false,"useJournalAbbreviation":true,"bibtexURL":"off","DOIandURL":"both","itemID":25614,"entry":"@article{davisComputingProcedureQuantification1960,\n  title = {A {{Computing Procedure}} for {{Quantification Theory}}},\n  author = {Davis, Martin and Putnam, Hillary},\n  year = {1960},\n  journal = {Journal of the ACM},\n  volume = {7},\n  number = {3},\n  pages = {201--215}\n}\n","metadata":{"DeclarePrefChars":"","noopsort":false,"packages":[]},"meta":{"revision":0,"created":1751534256145,"version":0,"updated":1753730283776},"$loki":1261},{"exportNotes":false,"useJournalAbbreviation":true,"bibtexURL":"off","DOIandURL":"both","itemID":25633,"entry":"@article{davisMachineProgramTheoremproving1962,\n  title = {A Machine Program for Theorem-Proving},\n  author = {Davis, Martin and Logemann, George and Loveland, Donald},\n  year = {1962},\n  journal = {Commun. ACM},\n  volume = {5},\n  number = {7},\n  pages = {394--397},\n  publisher = {{ACM Press}},\n  address = {{New York, NY, USA}},\n  issn = {0001-0782},\n  doi = {http://doi.acm.org/10.1145/368273.368557}\n}\n","metadata":{"DeclarePrefChars":"","noopsort":false,"packages":[]},"meta":{"revision":0,"created":1751534256146,"version":0,"updated":1753730283776},"$loki":1262},{"exportNotes":false,"useJournalAbbreviation":true,"bibtexURL":"off","DOIandURL":"both","itemID":26478,"entry":"@article{davisModifyingSparseCholesky1999,\n  title = {Modifying a Sparse {{Cholesky}} Factorizatio